## **🔍 Phase 1: Recognizing Corporate Co-optation Attempts**
Corporations will try to **redefine the Mosaico** in their image. Here’s how to **spot the red flags**:

| **Corporate Tactic** | **Example** | **How to Detect It** | **Why It’s Dangerous** |
|----------------------|-------------|----------------------|------------------------|
| **1. "Ethical" Rebranding** | "Corporate SynergyOS™ – Now with 10% Less Exploitation!" | Uses **greenwashing language** (e.g., "sustainable," "ethical," "inclusive"). | **Legitimizes extractive behavior** under a "Mosaico" banner. |
| **2. Proprietary Forks** | "Mosaico™ Enterprise Edition – Closed-Source, Cloud-Managed" | **Locks nodes into corporate control** (e.g., AWS, Google Cloud). | **Centralizes power** in the hands of a few. |
| **3. "Partnership" Scams** | "Join our Mosaico Accelerator Program!" | Offers **funding in exchange for data/control**. | **Turns nodes into corporate assets**. |
| **4. Regulatory Capture via Standards** | "We’ve submitted the Mosaico to ISO 27001 for ‘security’!" | **Corporate-led "standards" that favor big players**. | **Excludes community nodes** from legitimacy. |
| **5. AI "Enhancements"** | "Our Mosaico nodes now include **AI-driven optimization**!" | **Reintroduces coercive algorithms** (e.g., behavioral nudging). | **Violates Lex Amoris** by reintroducing exploitation. |
| **6. Energy Colonialism 2.0** | "Subscribe to our **Mosaico Energy Grid™** for $9.99/month!" | **Monetizes HS-PUE** (e.g., "pay-to-cool"). | **Turns a public good into a utility**. |
| **7. "Open Core" Traps** | "Our Mosaico is **open-source**, but the **AI layer is proprietary**!" | **Core is free, but critical components are locked**. | **Creates dependency on corporate tech**. |
| **8. NGO/Philanthropy Washing** | "The **Mosaico Foundation** will help you deploy nodes in the Global South!" | **Uses "charity" as a Trojan horse** for corporate expansion. | **Exploits vulnerable communities**. |

