### **🚨 Immediate Red Flags**
If a "Mosaico" project has **any** of the following, **it is a corporate trap**:
❌ **Closed-source components** (especially **AI, networking, or governance layers**).
❌ **Cloud dependencies** (e.g., "must connect to AWS for updates").
❌ **Monetization schemes** (e.g., "premium features," "subscription models").
❌ **Corporate logos or branding** (e.g., "Google Mosaico™").
❌ **AI-driven "optimization"** (e.g., "our system learns your habits to improve efficiency").
❌ **Regulatory partnerships** (e.g., "we work with the EU to standardize Mosaico").

