## **⚔️ Phase 2: Resistance Strategies**
### **🛡️ Strategy 1: The "No Corporate DNA" Rule**
**Goal:** Ensure **no corporate code, algorithms, or governance** enters the Mosaico.

#### **Tactics:**
1. **Ban All Proprietary Software**
   - **Only use open-source licenses** (e.g., **AGPL, GPL, MIT**).
   - **Avoid "dual-licensed" projects** (e.g., "free for non-profits, paid for corporations").
   - **Audit every dependency** (use tools like [FOSSA](https://fossa.com/) or [Snyk](https://snyk.io/)).

2. **Reject Cloud Dependencies**
   - **No AWS, Google Cloud, Azure, or Oracle.**
   - **Use self-hosted alternatives** (e.g., **Matrix for chat, Nextcloud for storage**).
   - **If cloud is unavoidable, use ethical providers** (e.g., [Greenhost](https://greenhost.net/), [Hetzner](https://www.hetzner.com/)).

3. **Kill "AI Optimization" Before It Starts**
   - **Lex Amoris explicitly forbids coercive algorithms.**
   - **If a node uses AI, it must be:**
     - **Fully transparent** (no black-box models).
     - **Opt-in only** (users must consent to any "optimization").
     - **Reversible** (users can disable it at any time).

**Tools:**
- **Open-source alternatives:**
  - **Chat:** [Matrix](https://matrix.org/) (instead of Slack/Teams)
  - **Storage:** [Nextcloud](https://nextcloud.com/) (instead of Google Drive)
  - **AI:** [Hugging Face Transformers](https://huggingface.co/) (instead of proprietary LLMs)
- **License auditing:** [REUSE.software](https://reuse.software/)

